  "local_port": 48534,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My friend block a person on what's app how could I know really he is blocked?",
  "response": "If your friend has blocked someone on WhatsApp, the blocked person will experience several changes in their interaction with your friend's account. Here's how you can determine if someone has been blocked:\n\n### Signs That You Have Been Blocked:\n1. **Last Seen and Online Status**:\n   - You won\u2019t be able to see the person\u2019s \"Last Seen\" timestamp or online status.\n\n2. **Profile Picture**:\n   - The profile picture will no longer be visible to you.\n\n3. **Status Updates**:\n   - You won\u2019t be able to see their status updates.\n\n4. **Message Delivery**:\n   - When you send a message, it will only show one gray tick (message sent) and won\u2019t show the second tick (message delivered), even if the person is online.\n\n5. **Calls**:\n   - You won\u2019t be able to call them. If you try, the call won\u2019t go through.\n\n### Other Things to Note:\n- **Group Chats**: If you and the person who blocked you are in the same group, you can still see their messages in the group chat, but you won\u2019t be able to see their profile picture or status updates.\n- **Profile Changes**: If the person changes their profile picture or status, you won\u2019t see those updates if you\u2019re blocked.\n\n### What Doesn\u2019t Happen:\n- **Contact Removal**: Being blocked doesn\u2019t remove the person from your contact list. You\u2019ll still see their name and number in your contacts, but with the above restrictions.\n\n### Important Note:\nThese signs can also occur if the person has simply deleted their WhatsApp account or if they have restricted their privacy settings. To be certain, you\u2019d need to check for multiple signs or ask someone else to check their interaction with the person in question.\n\nIf you suspect you\u2019ve been blocked, it\u2019s best to respect the person\u2019s decision and avoid confronting them about it.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
